# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Optional GitHub Personal Access Token for the GitHub panel.
#
# You do NOT need one. Without it, GitHub API calls are anonymous and capped
# at 60 requests/hour — plenty for the panel's 60-minute refresh (2 calls).
# With a token, the limit rises to 5,000 requests/hour.
#
# To add one later:
#   1. Copy this file to `.env.local`  (already git-ignored — never committed).
#   2. Create a token at https://github.com/settings/tokens
#      A classic token with NO scopes, or a fine-grained token with read-only
#      access to public repos, is enough — the panel only reads public data.
#   3. Paste it below the `VITE_GITHUB_TOKEN=` line in `.env.local`.
#   4. Restart `npm run tauri dev` so Vite picks up the new value.
#
# The VITE_ prefix is required for Vite to expose the value to the app.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
VITE_GITHUB_TOKEN=
